Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into 1cm wide strips. Halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1} in 1cm slices. Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then halve lengthways and separate the leaves then cut each leaf in half lengthways.

Combine the sweet potato, red pepper and red onion into a #mixing bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and half of the @chipotle paste{20%g} and half of the @smoked paprika{1%tsp}. Drizzle with @oil{} and mix well to combine. Put the veggies in a single layer on a #baking tray{} and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> TIP: Use 2 trays if needed.

Heat a splash of oil in a #large frying pan{} over a medium high heat. When hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g} and cook until golden brown all over, ~{7-10%minutes}. Once the chicken is golden, add the remaining smoked paprika and @honey{15%g}, cook until the chicken is coated and shiny, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, zest and halve your @lime{1}(zested and halved). In a #small bowl{} combine the lime zest, half the juice and the @mayonnaise{1}. Mix well and season to taste with salt and pepper.

> TIP: The dressing needs to be a pourable consistency, add a little water if it's too thick.

When the chicken is glazed, add the drained sweetcorn, the @BBQ sauce{32%g} and the remaining chipotle. Cook stirring frequently until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat. While the chicken cooks, slice the @halloumi{250%g} into 3 slices per person. Pop another #frying pan{} on high heat. Add a drizzle of oil and lay in the halloumi slices. Fry until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes} each side. Remove the pan from the heat.

Divide the sweet potato mix and baby gem between #bowls{}, top with the chicken and sweetcorn mix. Lay the halloumi slices on top, drizzle over the lime dressing and enjoy!